name: BitcoinGathering
description:
BTC Compound & Accumulation Bot


Part of a "Portfolio of Portfolios" with uncorrelated assets, by taking advantage on every 1% Market Move.

In Bull it partially SELLs the Base Asset, also BUYs back on Corrections. While in Bear it BUYs Base Assets, also SELL some, on Corrections.


Why Single Coin?


Multi assets portfolios with rebalance feature redistribute profits into dropping coins. We decide which ones worth it,
depending on the Market Cycles. Or we just let it run forever, to accumulate more.


Why Sub-Accounts?


We can use unlimited Exchanges. But only 5 Portfolios each. By using Subs it's like having a new Exchange.

And every Exchange allows us to use 100+ Sub-Accounts.


Required Funds?


$250+ each Portfolio. If you're low on cash you can start with Kucoin cause lowest limit per trade.


How to build your "Super Portfolio"?


We plan to have 30 Portfolios vs USDt on one Exchange. And for not placing "all eggs into the same basket", we continue to create 30 new Portfolios on 2nd and/or 3rd Exchange.

Then we come back to build more up, with the same 30 coins vs BTC and 30 vs ETH. 


Money Management


Active: for low funds, once running in profit you can take funds out at each 5%-10% (for later refills or to build new Portfolios with new savings). 

Passive: if you start with 30x$250 Portfolios on at least 2 x Exchanges you can come and take some profits to help you build up the 3rd Exchange.

name: 1INCHGATHERING
description:
1INCH Compound & Accumulation Bot


Part of a "Portfolio of Portfolios" with uncorrelated assets, by taking advantage on every 1% Market Move.

In Bull it partially SELLs the Base Asset, also BUYs back on Corrections. While in Bear it BUYs Base Assets, also SELL some, on Corrections.


Why Single Coin?


Multi assets portfolios with rebalance feature redistribute profits into dropping coins. We decide which ones worth it,
depending on the Market Cycles. Or we just let it run forever, to accumulate more.


Why Sub-Accounts?


We can use unlimited Exchanges. But only 5 Portfolios each. By using Subs it's like having a new Exchange.

And every Exchange allows us to use 100+ Sub-Accounts.


Required Funds?


$250+ each Portfolio. If you're low on cash you can start with Kucoin cause lowest limit per trade.


How to build your "Super Portfolio"?


We plan to have 30 Portfolios vs USDt on one Exchange. And for not placing "all eggs into the same basket", we continue to create 30 new Portfolios on 2nd and/or 3rd Exchange.

Then we come back to build more up, with the same 30 coins vs BTC and 30 vs ETH. 


Money Management


Active: for low funds, once running in profit you can take funds out at each 5%-10% (for later refills or to build new Portfolios with new savings). 

Passive: if you start with 30x$250 Portfolios on at least 2 x Exchanges you can come and take some profits to help you build up the 3rd Exchange.

name: ALGORANDGATHERING
description:
ALGO Compound & Accumulation Bot


Part of a "Portfolio of Portfolios" with uncorrelated assets, by taking advantage on every 1% Market Move.

In Bull it partially SELLs the Base Asset, also BUYs back on Corrections. While in Bear it BUYs Base Assets, also SELL some, on Corrections.


Why Single Coin?


Multi assets portfolios with rebalance feature redistribute profits into dropping coins. We decide which ones worth it,
depending on the Market Cycles. Or we just let it run forever, to accumulate more.


Why Sub-Accounts?


We can use unlimited Exchanges. But only 5 Portfolios each. By using Subs it's like having a new Exchange.

And every Exchange allows us to use 100+ Sub-Accounts.


Required Funds?


$250+ each Portfolio. If you're low on cash you can start with Kucoin cause lowest limit per trade.


How to build your "Super Portfolio"?


We plan to have 30 Portfolios vs USDt on one Exchange. And for not placing "all eggs into the same basket", we continue to create 30 new Portfolios on 2nd and/or 3rd Exchange.

Then we come back to build more up, with the same 30 coins vs BTC and 30 vs ETH. 


Money Management


Active: for low funds, once running in profit you can take funds out at each 5%-10% (for later refills or to build new Portfolios with new savings). 

Passive: if you start with 30x$250 Portfolios on at least 2 x Exchanges you can come and take some profits to help you build up the 3rd Exchange.
